      "sortOrder": 1,
      "title": "Day 12 — Your First Business Tool",
      "body": "Every entrepreneur needs a way to diagnose customer problems.",
      "speakerNotes": "Open: Yesterday you saw the opportunity. Today you get your first business tool.\nNot paperwork. A diagnostic instrument.",
      "discussionQuestions": [
        "What tools do other businesses use to understand customers?"
      ],
      "imageUrl": "/content/segment-1/week-3/day-2/deck-01/slide-01.png"
    },
    {
      "id": "slide-w3-d2-dk1-02",
      "presentationId": "presentation-w3-d2-deck-01",
      "sortOrder": 2,
      "title": "How Businesses Diagnose Problems",
      "body": "Restaurants taste food.\nDoctors diagnose patients.\nMechanics inspect vehicles.\nFinancial Advisors conduct an FNA.",
      "speakerNotes": "Walk through each example.\nEmphasize: professionals diagnose before they prescribe.\nFNA is the advisor's diagnostic — a business tool.",
      "discussionQuestions": [
        "What happens when a business skips diagnosis?"
      ],
      "imageUrl": "/content/segment-1/week-3/day-2/deck-01/slide-02.png"
    },
    {
      "id": "slide-w3-d2-dk1-03",
      "presentationId": "presentation-w3-d2-deck-01",
      "sortOrder": 3,
      "title": "FNA — Business Tool, Not Paperwork",
      "body": "Discover → Quantify → Prioritize → Plan",
      "speakerNotes": "Reframe FNA entirely.\nNo product language.\nThis is how your venture understands client needs before creating value.",
      "discussionQuestions": [],
      "imageUrl": "/content/segment-1/week-3/day-2/deck-01/slide-03.png"
    },
    {
      "id": "slide-w3-d2-dk1-04",
      "presentationId": "presentation-w3-d2-deck-01",
      "sortOrder": 4,
      "title": "Ethical Boundaries",
      "body": "No product talk until needs are documented.",
      "speakerNotes": "Entrepreneurs who rush to sell lose trust.\nAdvisors who rush to products lose clients.",
      "discussionQuestions": [],
      "imageUrl": "/content/segment-1/week-3/day-2/deck-01/slide-04.png"
    },
